            <h1 class="home-section__heading home-section__heading--indent-large"><span data-sr-chain="3" data-sr-order="1">Reducing</span> <strong data-sr-chain="3" data-sr-order="2">Risk of Use</strong></h1>
                    <img data-sr data-sr-distance="0" data-sr-viewfactor=".55" class="section__image section__image--right" src="https://www.globalzero.org/wp-content/uploads/2019/03/NFU-Homepage.png" alt="" />
            <div data-sr-chain="3" data-sr-order="3" data-sr-distance="0" class="section__text section__text--left">
      <p>We are at a turning point: The world has never faced so many nuclear flashpoints simultaneously and the risk that nuclear weapons will be used &#8212; intentionally, mistakenly or accidentally &#8212; is the highest it’s been since the height of the Cold War.</p>
<p>In response to the growing threat of nuclear use, Global Zero launched the global “No First Use” campaign to convince the world’s nine nuclear-armed nations to commit to never using nuclear weapons first. We’re working to strengthen the taboo against nuclear weapons use internationally, reducing reliance on nuclear weapons in national security and setting the stage for the complete elimination of nuclear weapons everywhere.</p>
      </div>
      

